UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1412
1 WHEREAS, continuing the tradition, sisters will mark their brothers' foreheads
2 with a unique tika symbolizing love and prayers for protection and prosperity. As a sign
3 of gratitude for their blessing, the brothers will give back to their sisters presents or cash;
4 and
5 WHEREAS, Holi is celebrated as a victory of life over the cold dark winter,
6 welcoming the arrival of spring; and
7 WHEREAS, during Holi, Hindus celebrate Prahlada's victory over Holika, as a
8 victory of good over evil, reinforcing the belief in righteousness prevailing; and
9 WHEREAS, to celebrate Holi, Hindus play with bright color powders, spray
10 colored water on each other and throw colored-water balloons. It is believed that the
11 combination of different colors takes all of the sorrow away and makes life itself more
12 colorful; and
13 WHEREAS, in their exercise of promoting individual and collective well-being,
14 truthfulness, compassion, and generosity, the Hindu people through their traditions and
15 customs have made a positive and lasting impact on this Commonwealth;
16 NOW, THEREFORE,
17 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
18 Commonwealth of Kentucky:
19 Section 1. The House of Representatives hereby recognizes the Hindu holidays
20 of Holi, March 4, 2026; Dashain and Vijaya Dashaimi, October 21, 2026; Laxmi Pooja,
21 Dipawali, and Diwali, November 9, 2026; and Bhaitika, November 11, 2026, and
22 encourages all residents of the Commonwealth to celebrate these days to honor and
23 reflect upon the significant contributions of the Hindu people to this Commonwealth.
24 Section 2. The Clerk of the House of Representatives is directed to transmit a
25 copy of this Resolution to Representative Daniel Grossberg.
